Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on investigating the performance of mobile user connectivity in femtocell/macrocell networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the interplays between outage probability and spectral efficiency in femtocell/macrocell networks, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the connectivity probability of mobile users in coexisting femtocell/macrocell networks, which can be considered as a social network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve multimedia applications in femtocell/macrocell networks, which can be related to multimedia. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may discuss the security and privacy issues in femtocell/macrocell networks, which can be related to cryptography and security.
